sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter (lambda cI and luxR regulated -- hybrid)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
cI repressor negatively regulates this promoter and LuxR activates its transcription.The effect of cI is dominant over LuxR. This part is based on the LuxR and cI repressor regulated hybrid promoter designed and tested by Ron Weiss. It requires the binding of two cI repressor dimers for maximal repression and contains two cI repressor binding sites namely, OR1 and OR2. This promoter is leaky in the sense that 'some' transcription is seen in the absence of both cI and LuxR.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI+pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: represillator of Elowitz and Leibler (2000)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The PLlac 0-1 promoter is a hybrid regulatory region consisting of the promoter P(L) of phage lambda with the cI binding sites replaced with lacO1. The hybrid design allows for strong promotion that can nevertheless be tightly repressed by LacI, the Lac inhibitor (i.e. repressor) (BBa_C0010) ([LUTZ97]). The activity of the promoter can be regulated over a >600-fold range by IPTG in E.Coli DH5-alpha-Z1 (same paper reference).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
hybrid promoter design to create strong promoter that is, at the same time, highly repressible. note that the upstream operator installed in this hybrid is slightly different than the one in the original source (Lutz and Bujard, 1997). the most upstream operator region is slightly truncated in the represillator version, so that both operators in the hybrid are the same sequence. see references for details. also, the sequence has been truncated after the transcriptional start site.

LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and increase transcription. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Neelaksh Varshney, Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Samantha Sutton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
We take advances in genetic engineering as synthetic biology, as viable solution to oil pollution cleanup. But for do this; we need to design and build an expression platform that works into our modified E.coli. For this, We choose four standardized biological parts from the Registry, those parts are: IPTG inducible promoter, Ribosomal Binding Site (RBS), GFP Reporter and Double Terminator; Were selected using rationale from molecular biology and genetic engineering to enable us to build up rationally-engineered, our expression platform.
For the iGEM 2011, we will integrate and assembly those parts (P+RBS+GFP+T) along with our BioBrick part using the 3A Assembly Method, to bring up an expression device (P+RBS+rhlAB_BB+GFP+T) for rhamnolipid production in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The part BBa_J04500 was used as a template for the creation of this new part. The -35 and -10 promoter elements were converted through mutagenesis into AflII and ClaI (respectively) restriction sites. A double restriction digest was performed and a T7 promoter was introduced in the form of primers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We wanted a T7 promoter that could be regulated with the lac system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Florencia Camus

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The iGEM Team Panama 2011 have to design and assemble the ends of an expression platform in order to bring up by rational designing a fuctional test platform for the expression of our Team favorite BioBrick part BBa_K653000 A.K. The Biosurfactator.
We choose to assembly two existing BioBrick parts from the shop, we mean The Registry. Those parts are: a GFP reporter BBa_E0040 and a double terminator BBa_B0015. We assemble them to bring up a new composite part that will serve as a well characterized ends for a expression platform for several coding sequences like our RhlAB_BBa_K653000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
This GFP part was derived from the reporter device used by Elowitz's repressilator : GFPmut3* has a couple of mutations from wtGFP - S2R and S65G and S72A. Emerald and EGFP have S65T and multiple other mutations. The S2R mutation should have no effect.
The Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012. This is the most commonly used terminator. It seems to be reliable.
The assembling of this two parts was performed using the 3A Assembly Method.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ernesto G??mez
